<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-10">Last updated: February 2026</p>

  <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-8">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What We Collect</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">When you use Community Notes Everywhere, we collect the following information:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>X (Twitter) profile information:</strong> Your public handle, display name, avatar, follower count, and account creation date. This is collected when you sign in via OAuth.</li>
        <li><strong>Notes you write:</strong> The text of your notes, the selected text they reference, and the page URL where they are posted.</li>
        <li><strong>Ratings you submit:</strong> Your helpfulness ratings on other users' notes.</li>
        <li><strong>Page URLs:</strong> The URLs of pages where notes are created or viewed, used to associate notes with the correct content.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li>Display your notes and ratings to other users</li>
        <li>Calculate your reputation score based on rating accuracy</li>
        <li>Determine your eligibility to write notes (reputation threshold)</li>
        <li>Associate notes with the correct webpages</li>
        <li>Moderate content through community reporting</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What We Don't Do</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
        <li>We <strong>do not sell</strong> your personal data to third parties</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not track</strong> your general browsing activity &mdash; we only see page URLs when you or others interact with notes on that page</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not use</strong> your data for advertising</li>
        <li>We <strong>do not share</strong> your data with third parties except as required by law</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data Retention</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">We retain your account data and contributions (notes, ratings) for as long as your account is active. If you wish to delete your account and associated data, please contact us. Notes you have written may be retained in anonymized form if they have been rated as helpful by the community.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Security</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">We use HTTPS for all communications. Authentication tokens are generated securely and stored hashed. We follow industry-standard practices to protect your data.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600">If you have questions about this privacy policy, please <a href="https://github.com/henryaj/community-notes-everywhere/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">open an issue on our GitHub repository</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
